HEADWORD: offhanded
<hw>offhanded</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>same as
<er>offhand</er> and <er>off-the-cuff</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ad-lib, extemporaneous, extemporary, extempore,
offhand, off-the-cuff, unpremeditated, unrehearsed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without, or seeming to be without, plan or method;
